{
  "texts": [
    "Three widely recognized metrics are BLEU [34], ROUGE [35], and METEOR [36].",
    "BLEU measures the correspondence between a machine-generated output and a human by comparing the co-occurrence of n-grams (word pairs, triples, etc.)",
    "in the generated text to a set of reference texts and calculates a score based on this comparison.",
    "High BLEU scores indicate a greater similarity to the reference texts, suggesting better output quality.",
    "ROUGE is typically used in summarization tasks."
  ]
}